#: ../../../topics/asyncio.rst:5
msgid "asyncio"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/asyncio.rst:7
msgid ""
"Scrapy has partial support for :mod:`asyncio`. After you :ref:`install the "
"asyncio reactor <install-asyncio>`, you may use :mod:`asyncio` and :mod:"
"`asyncio`-powered libraries in any :doc:`coroutine <coroutines>`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/asyncio.rst:15
msgid "Installing the asyncio reactor"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/asyncio.rst:17
msgid ""
"To enable :mod:`asyncio` support, your :setting:`TWISTED_REACTOR` setting "
"needs to be set to ``'twisted.internet.asyncioreactor."
"AsyncioSelectorReactor'``, which is the default value."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/asyncio.rst:21
msgid ""
"If you are using :class:`~scrapy.crawler.AsyncCrawlerRunner` or :class:"
"`~scrapy.crawler.CrawlerRunner`, you also need to install the :class:"
"`~twisted.internet.asyncioreactor.AsyncioSelectorReactor` reactor manually. "
"You can do that using :func:`~scrapy.utils.reactor.install_reactor`:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/asyncio.rst:28
msgid ""
"install_reactor(\"twisted.internet.asyncioreactor.AsyncioSelectorReactor\")"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/asyncio.rst:36
msgid "Handling a pre-installed reactor"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/asyncio.rst:38
msgid ""
"``twisted.internet.reactor`` and some other Twisted imports install the "
"default Twisted reactor as a side effect. Once a Twisted reactor is "
"installed, it is not possible to switch to a different reactor at run time."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/asyncio.rst:42
msgid ""
"If you :ref:`configure the asyncio Twisted reactor <install-asyncio>` and, "
"at run time, Scrapy complains that a different reactor is already installed, "
"chances are you have some such imports in your code."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/asyncio.rst:46
msgid ""
"You can usually fix the issue by moving those offending module-level Twisted "
"imports to the method or function definitions where they are used. For "
"example, if you have something like:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/asyncio.rst:51
msgid ""
"from twisted.internet import reactor\n"
"\n"
"\n"
"def my_function():\n"
"    reactor.callLater(...)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/asyncio.rst:59
msgid "Switch to something like:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/asyncio.rst:61
msgid ""
"def my_function():\n"
"    from twisted.internet import reactor\n"
"\n"
"    reactor.callLater(...)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/asyncio.rst:68
msgid ""
"Alternatively, you can try to :ref:`manually install the asyncio reactor "
"<install-asyncio>`, with :func:`~scrapy.utils.reactor.install_reactor`, "
"before those imports happen."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/asyncio.rst:76
msgid "Integrating Deferred code and asyncio code"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/asyncio.rst:78
msgid ""
"Coroutine functions can await on Deferreds by wrapping them into :class:"
"`asyncio.Future` objects. Scrapy provides two helpers for this:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../scrapy/utils/defer.py:docstring of
#: scrapy.utils.defer.deferred_to_future:1
msgid "Return an :class:`asyncio.Future` object that wraps *d*."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../scrapy/utils/defer.py:docstring of
#: scrapy.utils.defer.deferred_to_future:3
msgid ""
"This function requires :class:`~twisted.internet.asyncioreactor."
"AsyncioSelectorReactor` to be installed."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../scrapy/utils/defer.py:docstring of
#: scrapy.utils.defer.deferred_to_future:7
msgid ""
"When :ref:`using the asyncio reactor <install-asyncio>`, you cannot await "
"on :class:`~twisted.internet.defer.Deferred` objects from :ref:`Scrapy "
"callables defined as coroutines <coroutine-support>`, you can only await on "
"``Future`` objects. Wrapping ``Deferred`` objects into ``Future`` objects "
"allows you to wait on them::"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../scrapy/utils/defer.py:docstring of
#: scrapy.utils.defer.deferred_to_future:13
msgid ""
"class MySpider(Spider):\n"
"    ...\n"
"    async def parse(self, response):\n"
"        additional_request = scrapy.Request('https://example.org/price')\n"
"        deferred = self.crawler.engine.download(additional_request)\n"
"        additional_response = await deferred_to_future(deferred)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../scrapy/utils/defer.py:docstring of
#: scrapy.utils.defer.deferred_to_future:20
msgid ""
"This function no longer installs an asyncio loop if called before the "
"Twisted asyncio reactor is installed. A :exc:`RuntimeError` is raised in "
"this case."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../scrapy/utils/defer.py:docstring of
#: scrapy.utils.defer.maybe_deferred_to_future:1
msgid ""
"Return *d* as an object that can be awaited from a :ref:`Scrapy callable "
"defined as a coroutine <coroutine-support>`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../scrapy/utils/defer.py:docstring of
#: scrapy.utils.defer.maybe_deferred_to_future:4
msgid ""
"What you can await in Scrapy callables defined as coroutines depends on the "
"value of :setting:`TWISTED_REACTOR`:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../scrapy/utils/defer.py:docstring of
#: scrapy.utils.defer.maybe_deferred_to_future:7
msgid ""
"When :ref:`using the asyncio reactor <install-asyncio>`, you can only await "
"on :class:`asyncio.Future` objects."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../scrapy/utils/defer.py:docstring of
#: scrapy.utils.defer.maybe_deferred_to_future:10
msgid ""
"When not using the asyncio reactor, you can only await on :class:`~twisted."
"internet.defer.Deferred` objects."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../scrapy/utils/defer.py:docstring of
#: scrapy.utils.defer.maybe_deferred_to_future:13
msgid ""
"If you want to write code that uses ``Deferred`` objects but works with any "
"reactor, use this function on all ``Deferred`` objects::"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../scrapy/utils/defer.py:docstring of
#: scrapy.utils.defer.maybe_deferred_to_future:16
msgid ""
"class MySpider(Spider):\n"
"    ...\n"
"    async def parse(self, response):\n"
"        additional_request = scrapy.Request('https://example.org/price')\n"
"        deferred = self.crawler.engine.download(additional_request)\n"
"        additional_response = await maybe_deferred_to_future(deferred)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/asyncio.rst:84
msgid ""
"If you don't need to support reactors other than the default :class:"
"`~twisted.internet.asyncioreactor.AsyncioSelectorReactor`, you can use :func:"
"`~scrapy.utils.defer.deferred_to_future`, otherwise you should use :func:"
"`~scrapy.utils.defer.maybe_deferred_to_future`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/asyncio.rst:89
msgid ""
"If you need to use these functions in code that aims to be compatible with "
"lower versions of Scrapy that do not provide these functions, down to Scrapy "
"2.0 (earlier versions do not support :mod:`asyncio`), you can copy the "
"implementation of these functions into your own code."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/asyncio.rst:95
msgid ""
"Coroutines and futures can be wrapped into Deferreds (for example, when a "
"Scrapy API requires passing a Deferred to it) using the following helpers:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../scrapy/utils/defer.py:docstring of
#: scrapy.utils.defer.deferred_from_coro:1
msgid ""
"Convert a coroutine or other awaitable object into a Deferred, or return the "
"object as is if it isn't a coroutine."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../scrapy/utils/defer.py:docstring of
#: scrapy.utils.defer.deferred_f_from_coro_f:1
msgid "Convert a coroutine function into a function that returns a Deferred."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../scrapy/utils/defer.py:docstring of
#: scrapy.utils.defer.deferred_f_from_coro_f:3
msgid ""
"The coroutine function will be called at the time when the wrapper is "
"called. Wrapper args will be passed to it. This is useful for callback "
"chains, as callback functions are called with the previous callback result."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../scrapy/utils/defer.py:docstring of
#: scrapy.utils.defer.ensure_awaitable:1
msgid "Convert any value to an awaitable object."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../scrapy/utils/defer.py:docstring of
#: scrapy.utils.defer.ensure_awaitable:3
msgid ""
"For a :class:`~twisted.internet.defer.Deferred` object, use :func:"
"`maybe_deferred_to_future` to wrap it into a suitable object. For an "
"awaitable object of a different type, return it as is. For any other value, "
"return a coroutine that completes with that value."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/asyncio.rst:106
msgid "Enforcing asyncio as a requirement"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/asyncio.rst:108
msgid ""
"If you are writing a :ref:`component <topics-components>` that requires "
"asyncio to work, use :func:`scrapy.utils.asyncio.is_asyncio_available` to :"
"ref:`enforce it as a requirement <enforce-component-requirements>`. For "
"example:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/asyncio.rst:113
msgid ""
"from scrapy.utils.asyncio import is_asyncio_available\n"
"\n"
"\n"
"class MyComponent:\n"
"    def __init__(self):\n"
"        if not is_asyncio_available():\n"
"            raise ValueError(\n"
"                f\"{MyComponent.__qualname__} requires the asyncio support. "
"\"\n"
"                f\"Make sure you have configured the asyncio reactor in the "
"\"\n"
"                f\"TWISTED_REACTOR setting. See the asyncio documentation "
"\"\n"
"                f\"of Scrapy for more information.\"\n"
"            )"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../scrapy/utils/asyncio.py:docstring of
#: scrapy.utils.asyncio.is_asyncio_available:1
msgid ""
"Check if it's possible to call asyncio code that relies on the asyncio event "
"loop."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../scrapy/utils/asyncio.py:docstring of
#: scrapy.utils.asyncio.is_asyncio_available:5
msgid ""
"This function returns ``True`` if there is a running asyncio event loop. If "
"there is no such loop, it returns ``True`` if the Twisted reactor that is "
"installed is :class:`~twisted.internet.asyncioreactor."
"AsyncioSelectorReactor`, returns ``False`` if a different reactor is "
"installed, and raises a :exc:`RuntimeError` if no reactor is installed."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../scrapy/utils/asyncio.py:docstring of
#: scrapy.utils.asyncio.is_asyncio_available:12
msgid ""
"Code that doesn't directly require a Twisted reactor should use this "
"function while code that requires :class:`~twisted.internet.asyncioreactor."
"AsyncioSelectorReactor` should use :func:`~scrapy.utils.reactor."
"is_asyncio_reactor_installed`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../scrapy/utils/asyncio.py:docstring of
#: scrapy.utils.asyncio.is_asyncio_available:17
msgid ""
"When this returns ``True``, an asyncio loop is installed and used by Scrapy. "
"It's possible to call functions that require it, such as :func:`asyncio."
"sleep`, and await on :class:`asyncio.Future` objects in Scrapy-related code."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../scrapy/utils/asyncio.py:docstring of
#: scrapy.utils.asyncio.is_asyncio_available:22
msgid ""
"When this returns ``False``, a non-asyncio Twisted reactor is installed. "
"It's not possible to use asyncio features that require an asyncio event loop "
"or await on :class:`asyncio.Future` objects in Scrapy-related code, but it's "
"possible to await on :class:`~twisted.internet.defer.Deferred` objects."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../scrapy/utils/asyncio.py:docstring of
#: scrapy.utils.asyncio.is_asyncio_available:28
msgid ""
"As this function uses :func:`asyncio.get_running_loop()`, it will only "
"detect the event loop if called in the same thread and from the code that "
"runs inside that loop (this shouldn't be a problem when calling it from code "
"such as spiders and Scrapy components, if Scrapy is run using one of the "
"supported ways)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../scrapy/utils/asyncio.py:docstring of
#: scrapy.utils.asyncio.is_asyncio_available:34
msgid ""
"This function now also returns ``True`` if there is a running asyncio loop, "
"even if no Twisted reactor is installed."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../scrapy/utils/reactor.py:docstring of
#: scrapy.utils.reactor.is_asyncio_reactor_installed:1
msgid ""
"Check whether the installed reactor is :class:`~twisted.internet."
"asyncioreactor.AsyncioSelectorReactor`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../scrapy/utils/reactor.py:docstring of
#: scrapy.utils.reactor.is_asyncio_reactor_installed:3
msgid "Raise a :exc:`RuntimeError` if no reactor is installed."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../scrapy/utils/reactor.py:docstring of
#: scrapy.utils.reactor.is_asyncio_reactor_installed:5
msgid ""
"In a future Scrapy version, when Scrapy supports running without a Twisted "
"reactor, this function won't be useful for checking if it's possible to use "
"asyncio features, so the code that that doesn't directly require a Twisted "
"reactor should use :func:`scrapy.utils.asyncio.is_asyncio_available` instead "
"of this function."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../scrapy/utils/reactor.py:docstring of
#: scrapy.utils.reactor.is_asyncio_reactor_installed:11
msgid ""
"In earlier Scrapy versions this function silently installed the default "
"reactor if there was no reactor installed. Now it raises an exception to "
"prevent silent problems in this case."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/asyncio.rst:135
msgid "Using Scrapy without a Twisted reactor"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/asyncio.rst:140
msgid ""
"This is currently experimental and may not be suitable for production use."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/asyncio.rst:142
msgid ""
"It's possible to use Scrapy without installing a Twisted reactor at all, by "
"setting the :setting:`TWISTED_REACTOR_ENABLED` setting to ``False``. In this "
"mode Scrapy will use the asyncio event loop directly, and most of the Scrapy "
"functionality will work in the same way."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/asyncio.rst:147
msgid "Doing this provides several benefits in certain use cases:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/asyncio.rst:149
msgid ""
"A Twisted reactor, once stopped, cannot be started again. This prevents, for "
"example, using several instances of :class:`~scrapy.crawler."
"AsyncCrawlerProcess` in the same process when they use a reactor, but with "
"``TWISTED_REACTOR_ENABLED=False`` it becomes possible."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/asyncio.rst:154
msgid ""
"There may be limitations imposed by :class:`~twisted.internet.asyncioreactor."
"AsyncioSelectorReactor` and related Twisted code, such as the requirement of "
"using :class:`~asyncio.SelectorEventLoop` on Windows (see :ref:`asyncio-"
"windows`), that do not apply if the reactor is not used."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/asyncio.rst:159
msgid ""
":class:`~twisted.internet.asyncioreactor.AsyncioSelectorReactor` manages the "
"underlying event loop, and while :class:`~scrapy.crawler.AsyncCrawlerRunner` "
"can use a pre-existing reactor which, in turn, can use a pre-existing event "
"loop, it's easier to use :class:`~scrapy.crawler.AsyncCrawlerRunner` with a "
"pre-existing loop directly."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/asyncio.rst:164
msgid "Omitting the reactor machinery may improve performance and reliability."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/asyncio.rst:167
msgid "Limitations"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/asyncio.rst:169
msgid ""
"As some Scrapy features and components require a reactor, they don't work "
"and are disabled without it. Replacements that don't require a reactor may "
"be added in future Scrapy versions. The following features are not available:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/asyncio.rst:173
msgid ""
"The default HTTP(S) download handler, :class:`~scrapy.core.downloader."
"handlers.http11.HTTP11DownloadHandler` (this is likely the biggest "
"difference; Scrapy provides an HTTP(S) download handler that doesn't require "
"a reactor and will be used instead of it: :class:`~scrapy.core.downloader."
"handlers._httpx.HttpxDownloadHandler`)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/asyncio.rst:178
msgid ":class:`~scrapy.core.downloader.handlers.ftp.FTPDownloadHandler`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/asyncio.rst:179
msgid ":class:`~scrapy.core.downloader.handlers.http2.H2DownloadHandler`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/asyncio.rst:180
msgid ":ref:`topics-shell`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/asyncio.rst:181
msgid ":ref:`topics-telnetconsole`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/asyncio.rst:182
msgid ""
":class:`~scrapy.crawler.CrawlerRunner` and :class:`~scrapy.crawler."
"CrawlerProcess` (:class:`~scrapy.crawler.AsyncCrawlerProcess` and :class:"
"`~scrapy.crawler.AsyncCrawlerRunner` are available)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/asyncio.rst:186
msgid "Twisted-specific DNS resolvers (the :setting:`DNS_RESOLVER` setting)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/asyncio.rst:187
msgid ""
"User and 3rd-party code that requires a reactor (see :ref:`below <asyncio-"
"without-reactor-migrate>` for examples)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/asyncio.rst:190
msgid ""
"Note that importing Twisted modules and, among other things, creating and "
"using :class:`~twisted.internet.defer.Deferred` objects doesn't require a "
"reactor, so code that uses :class:`~twisted.internet.defer.Deferred`, :class:"
"`~twisted.python.failure.Failure` and some other Twisted APIs will not "
"necessarily stop working."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/asyncio.rst:197
msgid "Other differences"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/asyncio.rst:199
msgid ""
"When :setting:`TWISTED_REACTOR_ENABLED` is set to ``False``, Scrapy will "
"change the defaults of some other settings:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/asyncio.rst:202
msgid ":setting:`TELNETCONSOLE_ENABLED` is set to ``False``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/asyncio.rst:203
msgid ""
"The ``\"http\"`` and ``\"https\"`` keys in :setting:`DOWNLOAD_HANDLERS_BASE` "
"are set to ``\"scrapy.core.downloader.handlers._httpx."
"HttpxDownloadHandler\"``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/asyncio.rst:205
msgid ""
"The ``\"ftp\"`` key in :setting:`DOWNLOAD_HANDLERS_BASE` is set to ``None``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/asyncio.rst:207
msgid ""
"Thus, :class:`~scrapy.core.downloader.handlers._httpx.HttpxDownloadHandler` "
"is used by default for making HTTP(S) requests. Please refer to its "
"documentation for its differences and limitations compared to :class:"
"`~scrapy.core.downloader.handlers.http11.HTTP11DownloadHandler`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/asyncio.rst:212
msgid ""
"Additionally, :class:`~scrapy.crawler.AsyncCrawlerProcess` will install a :"
"term:`meta path finder` that prevents :mod:`twisted.internet.reactor` from "
"being imported."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/asyncio.rst:219
msgid "Adding support to existing code"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/asyncio.rst:221
msgid ""
"Code that doesn't directly use Twisted APIs or APIs that depend on Twisted "
"ones doesn't need special support for running without a reactor."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/asyncio.rst:224
msgid "Here are some examples of APIs and patterns that need a replacement:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/asyncio.rst:226
msgid ""
"Using :meth:`reactor.callLater() <twisted.internet.base.ReactorBase."
"callLater>` for sleeping or delayed calls. You can use :meth:`asyncio.loop."
"call_later` instead."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/asyncio.rst:229
msgid ""
"Using :func:`twisted.internet.threads.deferToThread`, :meth:`reactor."
"callFromThread() <twisted.internet.base.ReactorBase.callFromThread>` and "
"related APIs to execute code in other threads. You can use :func:`asyncio."
"to_thread`, :meth:`asyncio.loop.call_soon_threadsafe` and related APIs "
"instead."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/asyncio.rst:234
msgid ""
"Using :class:`twisted.internet.task.LoopingCall` for scheduling repeated "
"tasks. As there is no direct replacement in the standard library, you may "
"need to write your own one using :func:`asyncio.sleep` in a task."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/asyncio.rst:237
msgid ""
"Using Twisted network client and server APIs (:meth:`reactor.connectTCP() "
"<twisted.internet.interfaces.IReactorTCP.connectTCP>`, :meth:`reactor."
"listenTCP() <twisted.internet.interfaces.IReactorTCP.listenTCP>`, :mod:"
"`twisted.web.client`, :mod:`twisted.mail.smtp` etc.). You can use other "
"built-in or 3rd-party libraries for this."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/asyncio.rst:243
msgid ""
"Using :class:`~scrapy.crawler.CrawlerProcess` or :class:`~scrapy.crawler."
"CrawlerRunner`. You should use :class:`~scrapy.crawler.AsyncCrawlerProcess` "
"or :class:`~scrapy.crawler.AsyncCrawlerRunner` respectively instead."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/asyncio.rst:247
msgid ""
"Checking whether ``asyncio`` support is available with :func:`scrapy.utils."
"reactor.is_asyncio_reactor_installed`. You should use :func:`scrapy.utils."
"asyncio.is_asyncio_available` instead."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/asyncio.rst:251
msgid "Scrapy provides unified helpers for some of these examples:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../scrapy/utils/asyncio.py:docstring of
#: scrapy.utils.asyncio.call_later:1
msgid "Schedule a function to be called after a delay."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../scrapy/utils/asyncio.py:docstring of
#: scrapy.utils.asyncio.call_later:3
msgid ""
"This uses either :meth:`asyncio.loop.call_later` or :meth:`reactor."
"callLater() <twisted.internet.base.ReactorBase.callLater>`, depending on "
"whether asyncio support is available."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../scrapy/utils/asyncio.py:docstring of
#: scrapy.utils.asyncio.create_looping_call:1
msgid "Create an instance of a looping call class."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../scrapy/utils/asyncio.py:docstring of
#: scrapy.utils.asyncio.create_looping_call:3
msgid ""
"This creates an instance of :class:`~scrapy.utils.asyncio."
"AsyncioLoopingCall` or :class:`~twisted.internet.task.LoopingCall`, "
"depending on whether asyncio support is available."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../scrapy/utils/asyncio.py:docstring of
#: scrapy.utils.asyncio.AsyncioLoopingCall:1
msgid ""
"A simple implementation of a periodic call using asyncio, keeping some API "
"and behavior compatibility with :class:`~twisted.internet.task.LoopingCall`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../scrapy/utils/asyncio.py:docstring of
#: scrapy.utils.asyncio.AsyncioLoopingCall:5
msgid ""
"The function is called every *interval* seconds, independent of the finish "
"time of the previous call. If the function  is still running when it's time "
"to call it again, calls are skipped until the function finishes."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../scrapy/utils/asyncio.py:docstring of
#: scrapy.utils.asyncio.AsyncioLoopingCall:9
msgid "The function must not return a coroutine or a ``Deferred``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../scrapy/utils/asyncio.py:docstring of
#: scrapy.utils.asyncio.run_in_thread:1
msgid "Call a function in a thread and return its result as a coroutine."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../scrapy/utils/asyncio.py:docstring of
#: scrapy.utils.asyncio.run_in_thread:3
msgid ""
"This uses either :func:`asyncio.to_thread` or :func:`twisted.internet."
"threads.deferToThread`, depending on whether asyncio support is available."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/asyncio.rst:258
msgid ""
"If your code needs to know whether the reactor is available, you can either "
"check for the value of the :setting:`TWISTED_REACTOR_ENABLED` setting (you "
"need access to the :class:`~scrapy.crawler.Crawler` instance to do this) or "
"use the following function:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../scrapy/utils/reactorless.py:docstring of
#: scrapy.utils.reactorless.is_reactorless:1
msgid ""
"Check if we are running in the reactorless mode, i.e. with :setting:"
"`TWISTED_REACTOR_ENABLED` set to ``False``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../scrapy/utils/reactorless.py:docstring of
#: scrapy.utils.reactorless.is_reactorless:4
msgid ""
"As this checks the runtime state and not the setting itself, it can be wrong "
"when executed very early, before the reactor and/or the asyncio event loop "
"are initialized."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../scrapy/utils/reactorless.py:docstring of
#: scrapy.utils.reactorless.is_reactorless:8
msgid ""
"As this function uses :func:`scrapy.utils.asyncio.is_asyncio_available()`, "
"it has the same limitations for detecting a running asyncio event loop as "
"that one."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/asyncio.rst:265
msgid ""
"In general, code that doesn't use the reactor (directly or indirectly) can "
"be used unmodified both with the asyncio reactor and without a reactor. This "
"includes code that converts Deferreds to futures and vice versa as described "
"in :ref:`asyncio-await-dfd`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/asyncio.rst:271
msgid "Troubleshooting"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/asyncio.rst:273
msgid ""
"**ImportError: Import of twisted.internet.reactor is forbidden when running "
"without a Twisted reactor [...]:** Scrapy is configured to run without a "
"reactor, but some code imported :mod:`twisted.internet.reactor`, most likely "
"because that code needs a reactor to be used. You need to stop using this "
"code or set :setting:`TWISTED_REACTOR_ENABLED` back to ``True``. It's also "
"possible that the reactor isn't really needed but was installed due to the "
"problem described in :ref:`asyncio-preinstalled-reactor`, in which case it "
"should be enough to fix the problematic imports."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/asyncio.rst:282
msgid ""
"**RuntimeError: TWISTED_REACTOR_ENABLED is False but a Twisted reactor is "
"installed:** Scrapy is configured to run without a reactor, but a reactor is "
"already installed before the Scrapy code is executed. If you are trying to "
"set :setting:`TWISTED_REACTOR_ENABLED` via :ref:`per-spider settings <spider-"
"settings>`, it's currently unsupported."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/asyncio.rst:288
msgid ""
"**RuntimeError: We expected a Twisted reactor to be installed but it isn't:"
"** Scrapy is configured to run with a reactor and not to install one, but a "
"reactor wasn't installed before the Scrapy code is executed. If you are "
"trying to set :setting:`TWISTED_REACTOR_ENABLED` via :ref:`per-spider "
"settings <spider-settings>`, it's currently unsupported."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/asyncio.rst:294
msgid ""
"**RuntimeError: <class> doesn't support TWISTED_REACTOR_ENABLED=False:** The "
"listed class cannot be used with :setting:`TWISTED_REACTOR_ENABLED` set to "
"``False``. There may be a replacement in the :ref:`documentation above "
"<asyncio-without-reactor>` or the documentation of the affected class."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/asyncio.rst:303
msgid "Windows-specific notes"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/asyncio.rst:305
msgid ""
"The Windows implementation of :mod:`asyncio` can use two event loop "
"implementations, :class:`~asyncio.ProactorEventLoop` (default) and :class:"
"`~asyncio.SelectorEventLoop`. However, only :class:`~asyncio."
"SelectorEventLoop` works with Twisted."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/asyncio.rst:310
msgid ""
"Scrapy changes the event loop class to :class:`~asyncio.SelectorEventLoop` "
"automatically when you change the :setting:`TWISTED_REACTOR` setting or "
"call :func:`~scrapy.utils.reactor.install_reactor`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/asyncio.rst:314
msgid ""
"Other libraries you use may require :class:`~asyncio.ProactorEventLoop`, e."
"g. because it supports subprocesses (this is the case with `playwright`_), "
"so you cannot use them together with Scrapy on Windows (but you should be "
"able to use them on WSL or native Linux)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/asyncio.rst:320
msgid ""
"This problem doesn't apply when not using the reactor, see :ref:`asyncio-"
"without-reactor`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/asyncio.rst:329
msgid "Using custom asyncio loops"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/asyncio.rst:331
msgid ""
"You can also use custom asyncio event loops with the asyncio reactor. Set "
"the :setting:`ASYNCIO_EVENT_LOOP` setting to the import path of the desired "
"event loop class to use it instead of the default asyncio event loop."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/asyncio.rst:339
msgid "Switching to a non-asyncio reactor"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/asyncio.rst:341
msgid ""
"If for some reason your code doesn't work with the asyncio reactor, you can "
"use a different reactor by setting the :setting:`TWISTED_REACTOR` setting to "
"its import path (e.g. ``'twisted.internet.epollreactor.EPollReactor'``) or "
"to ``None``, which will use the default reactor for your platform. If you "
"are using :class:`~scrapy.crawler.AsyncCrawlerRunner` or :class:`~scrapy."
"crawler.AsyncCrawlerProcess` you also need to switch to their Deferred-based "
"counterparts: :class:`~scrapy.crawler.CrawlerRunner` or :class:`~scrapy."
"crawler.CrawlerProcess` respectively."
msgstr ""
